node.title: Covid-19 vaccine Novavax approved for use in New Zealand
node.description: The Novavax Covid-19 vaccine has been approved in New Zealand for those aged 18 and over.
node.content:
["The Novavax Covid-19 vaccine has been approved in New Zealand for those aged 18 and over.", "", "
Vials with the Nuvaxovid vaccine against the Covid-19 coronavirus are seen at the CIZ Tegel vaccination center in Berlin. Photo: AFP or licensors
", "The first doses are expected to arrive this month.", "The Novavax vaccine Nuvaxovid is the fourth vaccine to be approved by Medsafe.", "Pfizer/BioNTech, AstraZeneca and Janssen are all approved for use in New Zealand.", "Nuvaxovid is a two-dose protein subunit vaccine."]
